title: Need related call count
caption: Need related call count within 7 January, 2020 to 31 August, 2022 in Austin, TX
insights: There was a high number of called related to COVID-19 after March 2020. This brought other associated issues immediately (i.e., community clinics, payment, financial, insurance assistance).

Although it took a while (1-3 months), the city of Austin developed some solutions for the community to coordinate such unexpected issues related to COVID 19 and they are all back to normal level (since Aug 2020).
The loss of income due to restrictions results in more calls for financial assistance.
The calls for monetary, food, and housing assistance increase in the first months of the pandemic.
By mid-May, the volume of financial assistance calls decreases temporarily, only to increase again a month later by mid-June.
The loss of employee-based health insurance also results in a relatively increased effort to acquire insurance, highlighting perhaps the need for a more comprehensive approach to health insurance.
